│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                  │
│                                                              │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------              │
│ ### 1. Understanding the Issue ###                           │
│ The assertion failure occurs because the VPlan cost model    │
│ and the legacy cost model disagree on the best vectorization │
│ factor (VF). Specifically, the `BestFactor.Width` (8) does   │
│ not match the `LegacyVF.Width` (4), and the additional       │
│ conditions in the assertion (e.g., `PlanForEarlyExitLoop` or │
│ `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications`) are not satisfied.  │
│                                                              │
│ ### 2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log ###                             │
│ The `opt` log indicates that the loop has an unpredictable   │
│ backedge-taken count, which complicates vectorization. The   │
│ Scalar Evolution analysis shows that `%select.next` is       │
│ variant, and the loop's trip count depends on `%n`. This     │
│ unpredictability likely affects the cost models' decisions.  │
│                                                              │
│ ### 3. Root Cause Analysis ###                               │
│ The disagreement arises because the VPlan-based cost model   │
│ and the legacy cost model evaluate the loop differently. The │
│ `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` function checks if   │
│ the VPlan includes optimizations not accounted for in the    │
│ legacy model. However, the debugger reveals that this        │
│ function cannot resolve certain symbols (e.g.,               │
│ `SeenInstrs`), suggesting incomplete or incorrect context    │
│ setup during the assertion check.                            │
│                                                              │
│ ### 4. Proposed Edit Points ###                              │
│ Edit the assertion at lines 7579-7584 in                     │
│ `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp` to include │
│ additional debugging information. This will help identify    │
│ why the conditions fail:                                     │
│                                                              │
│ ```cpp                                                       │
│ assert((BestFactor.Width == LegacyVF.Width ||                │
│ PlanForEarlyExitLoop ||                                      │
│         planContainsAdditionalSimplifications(getPlanFor(Bes │
│ tFactor.Width),                                              │
│                                               CostCtx,       │
│ OrigLoop) ||                                                 │
│         planContainsAdditionalSimplifications(getPlanFor(Leg │
│ acyVF.Width),                                                │
│                                               CostCtx,       │
│ OrigLoop)) &&                                                │
│        "VPlan cost model and legacy cost model disagreed.\n" │
│        "BestFactor.Width: " << BestFactor.Width << ",        │
│ LegacyVF.Width: " << LegacyVF.Width << "\n"                  │
│        "PlanForEarlyExitLoop: " << PlanForEarlyExitLoop);    │
│ ```                                                          │
│                                                              │
│ ### 5. Conclusion ###                                        │
│ The proposed change adds detailed debugging output to the    │
│ assertion, providing insights into the values of             │
│ `BestFactor.Width`, `LegacyVF.Width`, and                    │
│ `PlanForEarlyExitLoop`. This will help diagnose the root     │
│ cause of the disagreement between the cost models.           │
